  "prompt": "How do you treat numbness on the tongue?",
  "response": "Here are some ways to treat tongue numbness:\n\n1. Identify the cause\n- Possible causes include allergic reactions, nerve damage, infections, or medical conditions\n\n2. Medical treatments\n- Consult a doctor for proper diagnosis\n- Medications to address underlying conditions\n- Treatments for specific causes like vitamin deficiencies or nerve issues\n\n3. Home remedies\n- Rest and avoid potential irritants\n- Stay hydrated\n- Rinse with warm salt water\n- Use over-the-counter oral pain relief gels\n- Take vitamin B supplements if deficiency is suspected\n\n4. When to seek immediate medical attention\n- Numbness accompanied by:\n- Severe pain\n- Difficulty speaking\n- Swelling\n- Signs of allergic reaction\n- Sudden onset after head injury\n\n5. Prevention\n- Maintain good oral hygiene\n- Eat a balanced diet\n- Avoid known allergens\n- Manage underlying health conditions\n\nImportant: If numbness persists or is accompanied by other symptoms, consult a healthcare professional for proper diagnosis and treatment.",
